♪ I can see [indistinct]♪

29:23.674 --> 29:25.415
Chef Louise, wasn't it?

29:25.459 --> 29:26.939
Yeah. That's right.

29:26.982 --> 29:28.984
So good to see you,
Madam President.

29:29.028 --> 29:30.986
I never got the chance
to thank you for the part

29:31.030 --> 29:32.945
that you played in my rescue.

29:32.988 --> 29:34.729
Miss Batan.

29:34.773 --> 29:37.166
But that won't change
the past.

29:37.210 --> 29:38.951
There are many lives
that you still need

29:38.994 --> 29:40.953
to answer for.

29:40.996 --> 29:42.693
Can I finish my drink first?

29:45.087 --> 29:46.959
Make no mistake,

29:47.002 --> 29:49.178
your day of reckoning
is at hand.

29:52.094 --> 29:53.966
I understand.

29:54.009 --> 29:55.141
I won't run.

29:55.184 --> 29:56.577
Am I now to believe

29:56.620 --> 29:59.058
that you've had a change
of heart?

30:00.973 --> 30:05.934
Everything I did was meant
to save witches.

30:05.978 --> 30:07.631
I've seen the news.

30:07.675 --> 30:09.982
Camarilla are striking
all over the globe.

30:10.025 --> 30:13.376
Quartermain says the world
is burning and she's right.

30:14.900 --> 30:16.684
And although, I might not
have lit the match,

30:16.727 --> 30:18.860
I definitely poured fuel
on the fire,

30:18.904 --> 30:22.951
so I'm ready to own that.

30:22.995 --> 30:26.912
I just ask
is that you, somehow,

30:26.955 --> 30:30.002
use my knowledge
and experience to fight them.

30:32.700 --> 30:34.267
To be clear,

30:34.310 --> 30:38.706
a pardon is off
the table, understood?

30:39.707 --> 30:42.971
Yes, Madam President.

30:43.015 --> 30:46.279
[Tally moaning]

30:46.322 --> 30:49.238
[giggling]

30:49.282 --> 30:51.893
[breathing heavily]

30:53.982 --> 30:55.331
What?

30:55.375 --> 30:58.204
I feel like that painting
is judging us.

31:02.382 --> 31:04.297
Then let her watch.

31:06.255 --> 31:07.822
[exhales sharply]

31:07.866 --> 31:11.260
[moaning]

31:11.304 --> 31:13.915
[giggling]

31:17.919 --> 31:20.487
Your, uh--your mom
would have loved this.

31:20.530 --> 31:22.489
She would be so proud of you.

31:25.318 --> 31:26.623
I'm so sorry
I didn't tell you--

31:26.667 --> 31:27.929
Oh, hey, hey, hey, hey.

31:27.973 --> 31:29.409
Come on,
come on, come on come on.

31:29.452 --> 31:31.585
You were in
an impossible position.

31:31.628 --> 31:33.630
I understand that.

31:33.674 --> 31:35.284
It's about the only thing
in this whole situation

31:35.328 --> 31:36.982
that I do understand.

31:38.897 --> 31:40.289
I guess I can't be mad
at her for wanting

31:40.333 --> 31:42.901
to protect our little girl.

31:42.944 --> 31:45.251
Yes, you can dad!

31:45.294 --> 31:47.079
You should be.
We both should be.

31:47.122 --> 31:50.212
[stammers] She made
a terrible decision

31:50.256 --> 31:52.519
and we both had to pay
the price for that.

31:54.521 --> 31:56.131
Well--so where
does that leave us?

31:57.350 --> 31:58.786
I don't...

32:03.312 --> 32:05.575
I guess, we both have
to find a way to forgive her.

32:07.751 --> 32:09.753
Any clue how to go about that?

32:09.797 --> 32:12.017
No. I don't.

32:13.975 --> 32:16.325
But we can figure it
out together.

32:16.369 --> 32:17.457
Oh, we can.

32:20.808 --> 32:22.462
[sighs]
Love you, kid.

32:23.767 --> 32:25.247
I love you, dad.

32:28.990 --> 32:30.992
MINERVA:
Well, I told you she'd be here.

32:33.038 --> 32:37.651
You used to spend hours
just staring at this painting.

32:37.694 --> 32:41.002
Talking to Jem like you expected
her to talk back.

32:41.046 --> 32:44.440
I think this painting
is my earliest memory.

32:44.484 --> 32:48.923
I'm starting to wonder
if she's finally answering me.

32:48.967 --> 32:51.926
Or, maybe, talking through me...

32:51.970 --> 32:53.232
Give us a minute, mother.

32:53.275 --> 32:54.973
Mm-hmm.

32:58.019 --> 33:00.500
Ever since I first
tried Jem's Working,

33:00.543 --> 33:04.504
there has been something
growing inside of me.

33:04.547 --> 33:06.636
I felt it at
that airfield in the Cession,

33:06.680 --> 33:08.464
and again out on that road.

33:08.508 --> 33:10.510
I heard about the Razor Hail.

33:10.553 --> 33:12.512
No one from our line
has done that work before.

33:12.555 --> 33:14.209
But how do we know that?

33:14.253 --> 33:16.559
It's like grandma said:
so much of our history

33:16.603 --> 33:17.952
was stolen from us.

33:17.996 --> 33:20.999
Who knows
what we were capable of?

33:21.042 --> 33:24.698
There has to be a reason
the Camarilla were hunting us.

33:24.741 --> 33:26.961
Of course there is.

33:27.005 --> 33:29.137
They're afraid.

33:29.181 --> 33:31.052
They've been afraid
ever since Jem crushed

33:31.096 --> 33:33.663
a Camarilla's skull
with a whisper.

33:33.707 --> 33:36.579
[chuckles]
But, through it all,

33:36.623 --> 33:38.581
the one thing they could never
take from us

33:38.625 --> 33:40.757
was our Work.

33:40.801 --> 33:42.542
That is our true legacy.

33:48.461 --> 33:50.593
[sentry groans]

33:50.637 --> 33:53.031
[screams]
Help!

33:56.991 --> 33:58.949
[screaming]

34:02.301 --> 34:03.998
You here to finish the job?

34:04.042 --> 34:09.134
As a matter of fact,
we are here to finish the job.

34:09.177 --> 34:13.051
I hope you're feeling rested,
Mr. President.

34:16.619 --> 34:18.665
We have a lot to accomplish.

34:18.708 --> 34:22.364
[sinister music playing]

34:26.977 --> 34:29.110
[laughing]

34:30.851 --> 34:32.548
TALLY:
To the bride, and the bride,

34:32.592 --> 34:34.115
and the bride, and the groom.

34:34.159 --> 34:35.899
I will drink to each
and every one of them.

34:35.943 --> 34:37.640
-Cheers.
-Hear, hear.

34:40.034 --> 34:42.036
So Tal, did you see
any of this coming?

34:42.080 --> 34:45.300
Mm-mm. No.

34:45.344 --> 34:47.302
-But it's a nice surprise.
-[chuckles]

34:47.346 --> 34:48.956
Yeah, I definitely
didn't predict any of this.

34:48.999 --> 34:50.914
[laughing]

34:50.958 --> 34:53.047
-ADIL: [clears throat]
-I've got another surprise.

34:54.614 --> 34:56.181
-Oh.
-TALLY: [gasps] Yes.

34:56.224 --> 34:58.139
-ABIGAIL: Come on, shitbird.
-Yes!

34:58.183 --> 34:59.967
Everybody is always telling me
how great of a singer you are.

35:00.010 --> 35:01.577
You're a legend.
[clears throat]

35:01.621 --> 35:02.970
Where did you get my guitar?

35:03.013 --> 35:04.928
Well, we asked
your dad to bring it.

35:06.495 --> 35:08.193
Oh, you two
have been conspiring now?

35:08.236 --> 35:09.324
[laughing]

35:09.368 --> 35:10.717
This does not bode well

35:10.760 --> 35:12.153
for the future.

35:12.197 --> 35:15.548
-Come on, Rae. Please.
-It's my wedding.

35:15.591 --> 35:17.637
Isn't someone
supposed to sing to me?

35:17.680 --> 35:20.640
[singing]
♪ I love you, Raelle... ♪

35:20.683 --> 35:22.772
-[laughing]
-Okay, okay. I'll sing.

35:22.816 --> 35:23.904
I'll sing.

35:25.166 --> 35:26.733
All right.

35:29.823 --> 35:31.129
[clears throat]

35:38.005 --> 35:41.704
[guitar music playing]

35:48.581 --> 35:50.800
♪ I'll be your mirror ♪

35:50.844 --> 35:52.976
♪ Reflect what you are♪

35:53.020 --> 35:54.935
♪ In case you don't know♪

35:54.978 --> 35:57.894
♪ I'll be the wind♪

35:57.938 --> 35:59.896
♪ The rain, and the sunset♪

